The paper deals with the capacity of locally decodable codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the use of coding theory (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC) to analyze the performance of these codes. The paper also discusses the privacy-preserving aspect of the codes, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves mathematical analysis and proofs, which is a common theme in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
